  <abstract>Drawing of aerial view of the grounds of Carnton Plantation, home of Randal McGavock, in Franklin.</abstract>
  <abstract>Former Nashville Mayor Randal McGavock (1768-1843) built Carnton in 1826. The original home was a red brick Federal-style home. Later additions included the Greek Revival-style portico by McGavock's son, John McGavock. The home played an important role in the Civil War during the Battle of Franklin, with the house serving as a temporary field hospital. The McGavock Confederate Cemetery, a large military cemetery, is located on the property.</abstract>
